        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Adds a new synapse, returns its index. This is triggered by addMsg of inputs to the child synapse. The SynHandler has to ensure that we have enough synapses allocated to handle the new message, and the return value is used so that the new message knows the fieldIndex to send the message to. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
